This article is a summary of an executive order issued by President Biden on January 21, 2021. The order aims to combat the COVID-19 pandemic by securing necessary supplies, including personal protective equipment (PPE) and resources for testing and vaccination. The order directs various government agencies to review the availability of these supplies and assess the ability of US industry to provide them. If shortfalls are identified, the relevant agencies are instructed to take action, including using the Defense Production Act, to address the shortages. The Secretary of Health and Human Services is required to provide a report on the status of the Strategic National Stockpile. The order also addresses pricing of pandemic response supplies and calls for the development of a long-term strategy to manufacture supplies for future pandemics. It further emphasizes the importance of equitable distribution and access to supplies for Tribal authorities and healthcare providers. The order is to be implemented in accordance with applicable law and subject to the availability of appropriations.